The paper deals with compressed indexing, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The time-space trade-offs presented in the paper involve algorithms and data structures, which are also relevant to computational complexity (cs.CC) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper uses techniques from machine learning (cs.LG) to achieve its results.
